150 g Falafel
½ unit(s) Red Onion
2 tbsp Tahini Sauce
1 tbsp Mayonnaise
1 unit(s) Sweet Bell Pepper
7 g Cilantro
2 tbsp Mango Chutney
1 tbsp Hot Sauce
285 g Cauliflower
½ tbsp Jerk Spice Blend
310 g Chicken Breast Tenders
2 tbsp Oil*
0.13 tsp Salt*
0.13 tsp Pepper*

Cut cauliflower into bite-sized pieces.
Line a baking sheet with parchment paper.
Add cauliflower, half the Jerk Spice Blend (use all for 4 ppl) and 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) oil to the prepared baking sheet. Season with salt, then toss to combine. Roast in the middle of the oven until tender, 14-16 min.

Meanwhile, toss falafel with 1/2 tbsp (1 tbsp) oil on an unlined baking sheet. Roast in the middle of the oven, flipping halfway through, until golden-brown, 10-13 min.
Pat chicken dry with paper towels. Season with salt and pepper.
Heat a large non-stick pan over medium-high heat. When hot, add 1/2 tbsp (1 tbsp) oil, then chicken breast tenders. Sear until tenders are golden-brown and cooked through, 3-4 min per side.** Transfer to a plate.

Meanwhile, cut half the onion (use whole onion for 4 ppl) into 1/4-inch slices.
Core, then cut pepper into 1/2-inch pieces.
Roughy chop cilantro.
Add half the mayo (use all for 4 ppl) and tahini sauce to a small bowl. Whisk to combine, then set aside.

Heat the same pan over medium-high heat.
When hot, add 1/2 tbsp (1 tbsp) oil, then onions and peppers. Cook, stirring occasionally, until tender-crisp, 3-4 min.
Season with salt.

Add half the mango chutney and half the hot sauce (use all the chutney and hot sauce for 4 ppl) to a large bowl. Stir to combine.
When falafel is crispy, add to large bowl with mango-hot sauce mixture. Toss to coat.

Divide cauliflower, onions and peppers between bowls.
Thinly slice chicken.
Top with chicken and falafel, then drizzle any remaining mango-hot sauce over top.
Drizzle tahini mixture over top.
Sprinkle cilantro over top.

If you've opted to add chicken breast tenders, pat dry with paper towels. Season with salt and pepper. Heat a large non-stick pan over medium-high heat. When hot, add 1/2 tbsp (1 tbsp) oil, then chicken breast tenders. Sear until tenders are golden-brown and cooked through, 3-4 min per side.** Use the same pan to cook the veggies in step 4.

Thinly slice chicken. Top bowls with chicken.